    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if the evidence mostly shows it makes inequality worse, wouldn't it be accurate to say that these supply-side arguments are basically just used as a justification for policies that benefit the top 1%? like, is there any real intellectual merit left in them, or are they just politically convenient?",
